article.description: LOGAN, Utah (AP) -Stephen DuCharme scored 13 points to lead Utah State to a 65-49 win over Cal State Bakersfield Saturday night.
article.headline: LOGAN, Utah (AP) -Stephen DuCharme scored 13 points to lead Utah State to a 65-49 win over Cal State Bakersfield Saturday night.
article.linkText: LOGAN, Utah (AP) -Stephen DuCharme scored 13 points to lead Utah State to a 65-49 win over Cal State Bakersfield Saturday night.
article.story: Jaycee Carroll also scored 11 for the Aggies (10-3), recording double-figure scoring each game this season. The Roadrunners (4-6) were led by Carl Damus, with 12 points, and Dwuan Rice with 11. USU went on a 10-0 run with 9:15 left to play, capped off when O.J. Harrison ran the length of the court for a layup. After a jumper by Rice stopped the run, Carroll then scored on another fast break layup and USU extended their largest lead to 61-41. USU's bench outscored CSB's reserves 20-14. Thirty-three fouls were called in the game, with Utah State's Chris Session fouling out with 10 points. There were also 35 turnovers, 19 by the Roadrunners. Carroll, averaging 22 points per game, was held to only seven points in a low-scoring first half. USU's biggest lead of the first half, 21-13, came after Sessions scored eight points for the Aggies and helped USU to a 29-23 halftime edge
